   "source": [
    "This notebook is to prepare the replica path calculation\n",
    "\n",
    "Before setting up the path calculation one needs 2 end point structures. They can be anything we are interested of the system to go from one structure into another one.\n",
    "For example we want to go from structure qmdown_200.cor to qmup_100.cor in 17 steps.\n",
    "These are 2 symmetrical structures and we want odd number of replicas to catch the midlle one too, which is a candidate for a transition state.\n",
    "\n",
    "Usually one can just cut/paste this into an CHARMM input script\n",
    "\n",
    "-------------------------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "read coor card name qmdown_200.cor\n",
    "\n",
    "coor copy comp\n",
    "\n",
    "read coor card name qmup_100.cor\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "coor orien rms sele type c1 .or. type c2 .or. type c3 .or. type c4 -\n",
    "               .or. type c5 .or. type c6 show end\n",
    "\n",
    "set n 17\n",
    " \n",
    "replicate A nreplicate @n select all end\n",
    "\n",
    "set d 1.0\n",
    "set m @n\n",
    "decr m by 1\n",
    "divi d by @m\n",
    "set 1 1\n",
    "set a 0.0\n",
    "label loop\n",
    "  coor duplicate select all end select segid A@1 end\n",
    "  coor duplicate select all end select segid A@1 end comp\n",
    "  coor average fact @a  select segid A@1 end\n",
    "  ! repair hydrogens:\n",
    "  coor init sele segid A@1 .and. ( type h5 .or. type h6 ) show end\n",
    "  hbuild\n",
    "  increment a by @d\n",
    "  increment 1 by 1\n",
    "if @1 .le. @n goto loop\n",
    "\n",
    "! get rid of the original, we only want the replicas A1 - A17\n",
    "delete atom sele segi cou  end\n",
    "\n",
    "write coor card name qmrpath0r.cor\n",
    "\n",
    "open write unit 1 card name rpath.psf\n",
    "write psf card unit 1\n",
    "\n",
    "! ignore hydrogens\n",
    "scalar wmain set 0.0 sele all end\n",
    "scalar wmain set 1.0 sele type c* .or. type o* show end\n",
    "\n",
    "rpath krms 1000.0 kangle 100.0 cosmax 0.95 mass weight rotation translation\n",
    "\n",
    "! or one can also use cons harm instead of cons fix\n",
    "\n",
    "cons fix select segid A1 .or. segid A@n end\n",
    "\n",
    "--------------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "The rest of the file is the same as in simulation notebook: define link atoms, define gamess environment, select qm region and run mini or dynamics\n",
    "\n",
    "Again once psf and dcd files are written one can see the simulation with the vmd graphics.\n"
   ]
